
[1]orlop

   OR'LOP, n.

   In a ship of war, a platform of planks laid over the beams in the hold,
   on which the cables are usually coiled. It contains also sail-rooms,
   carpenters' cabins and other apartments.

   Also, a tier of beams below the lower deck for a like purpose.
